import React from 'react'; import './Resume.css'; const Resume = () => { return (

My Resume

{/* Summary Section */}

Summary

I am a software engineering student with a strong background in web development, cloud platforms (AWS), and experience in Agile environments. I also have professional experience as a German-qualified flight attendant, which provides me with unique insight into real-world user needs for application development in the airline industry.

{/* Experience Section */}

Professional Experience

Flight Attendant (German Qualified) - United Airlines

Responsibilities: Managed in-flight services, ensured customer satisfaction for nearly 300 passengers per flight, and served on long-haul international flights twice a week.
Key Accomplishments: Completed over 150 long-haul flights, served between 250-300 passengers in economy and 50 first-class passengers.

Web Developer - Brigham Young University

Contributed to the On-Campus Housing system, creating icons and several components still in use today. I used Mendix, JavaScript, HTML, CSS, and Bootstrap for development.
Also utilized Angular and React to build temporary functionality necessary for the housing ecosystem while permanent solutions were developed.

Barista - My Mom's Cafe, Salzburg, Austria

Provided excellent customer service in German and English, served specialty beverages, and managed cash transactions.
Key Accomplishment: Awarded 'Employee of the Month' for excellent performance.

{/* Education Section */}

Education

B.S. in Software Engineering (Expected January 2025) - Western Governors University

High School Graduate - Golf State Champion

{/* Certificates Section */}

Certificates

  • AWS Certified Cloud Practitioner
  • CompTIA Project+
  • Google IT Support Certificate
  • Deutsch B2 (Goethe-Institut)
); }; export default Resume;
